# Copy to `.env` and/or `.env.test` locally (do not commit real secrets).
#
# `npm run test:live-api` starts `npm run dev`, waits for GET /health on port 5000, then runs Vitest.
# If the API is already running elsewhere, use `npm run test:live-api:vitest` and set TEST_BASE_URL.
# This file or `.env` must define DATABASE_URL if you run tests/clinic-intake.test.ts
#      (Vitest loads `.env` then `.env.test` before live test files import server/db).

# NODE_ENV=test
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@localhost:5432/hospital_erp_test
# TEST_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:5000
# TEST_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
# TEST_ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin123
TEST_ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin123